ecognizes%20that%20older%20people%20have%20worked%20hard%2C%20so%20when%20people%20become%20elderly%2C%20basically%20every%20need%20is%20taken%20care%20of%20by%20their%20families.%20Then%2C%20in%20Columbia%2C%20many%20live%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20spend%20their%20lives%20working%20in%20the%20fields%20with%20their%20huge%20families%2C%20who%20all%20look%20after%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20suggests%20there%20is%20a%20link%20between%20strong%20relationships%20and%20longevity%2C%20with%20one%202023%20study%20finding%20that%20living%20alone%20and%20being%20isolated%20from%20family%20and%20friends%20was%20associated%20with%20a%2077%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvisit-family-friends-social-interaction-help-live-longer-study-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehigher%20risk%20of%20death.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20of%20the%20older%20people%20Villatoro%20has%20met%20in%20Argentina%20live%20in%20retirement%20homes%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethan%20in%20other%20countries.%20Although%2077%25%20of%20older%20people%20are%20looked%20after%20by%20their%20families%2C%20this%20is%20not%20as%20high%20as%20in%20Brazil%2C%20where%20the%20figure%20is%2094.1%25%2C%20according%20to%202023%20data%20from%20the%20Pan%20American%20Health%20Organisation%20and%20Inter-American%20Development%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYamamoto%20has%20noticed%20a%20similar%20trend%20in%20Japan%2C%20where%20she%20said%20more%20and%20more%20older%20people%20are%20moving%20into%20care%20homes%2C%20whereas%20traditionally%2C%20their%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20would%20have%20looked%20after%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcultural-differences-longevity-supercentenarian-secrets-habits-countries-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705143121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22